# RvsB Platform — Full Redesign Implementation Plan

This plan replaces the scripted agent prototype with a real, trainable, professional-grade security simulation platform suitable for corporate use.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Critical decision — AI Agent Backend (requires your choice):**
>
> | Option | Technology | Your GPU Load | Quality |
> |---|---|---|---|
> | **A — Pure RL** | PyTorch PPO/DQN | ~4 GB VRAM | Fast, deterministic, must train first |
> | **B — Local LLM** | Ollama + Llama3-8B-Q4 | ~6–8 GB VRAM | Reasoning out-of-box, slower per step |
> | **C — Hybrid (Recommended)** | RL policy + LLM reasoning layer | ~8–10 GB VRAM | Best of both: speed + intelligence |
>
> Option C is recommended: RL handles low-level actions (scan/exploit decisions), LLM generates human-readable reasoning logs and adapts high-level strategy.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Security Environment scope:**
> - **Option I — Simulated (current):** Fast, portable, no real attacks. Good for demos.
> - **Option II — Real Docker Services:** Vulnerable apps (DVWA, OpenSSH) in isolated Docker network. Authentic but requires Docker Desktop with enough RAM (recommended).
>
> Option II is recommended for corporate authenticity.

---

## Architecture Overview

```
+--------------------+        +--------------------+
|  RED TEAM AGENT    |        |  BLUE TEAM AGENT   |
|  RL Policy (PPO)   | <----> |  RL Policy (PPO)   |
|  + LLM Reasoning   |        |  + LLM Reasoning   |
|  + Memory Store    |        |  + Memory Store    |
+--------+-----------+        +-----------+--------+
         |   HTTP/REST                    |
         v                               v
+--------+--------------------------------+--------+
|         ENVIRONMENT SERVER (FastAPI)             |
|   Docker Network: DVWA + OpenSSH + FTP          |
|   Realistic services with real vulnerabilities  |
+--------------------------------------------------+
         |
         v
+--------------------+
|  REACT DASHBOARD   |
|  Live match view   |
|  Training graphs   |
|  Rating report     |
+--------------------+
```

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Environment — Authentic Docker Network
#### [MODIFY] `docker-compose.yml` (new full version)
- `env_server`: FastAPI orchestrator
- `dvwa`: Damn Vulnerable Web Application (real CVEs like SQLi, XSS)
- `openssh_target`: SSH server with weak credentials
- `ftp_target`: vsftpd with anonymous login enabled

#### [MODIFY] [src/envs/rvsb_env/server/environment.py](file:///d:/College/RvsB/src/envs/rvsb_env/server/environment.py)
- Replace toy simulation with real subprocess calls to `nmap`, `curl`, `ssh`
- Services are real Docker containers — attacks have real-world consequences within the sandbox

---

### 2. AI Agents — Trainable RL + LLM Reasoning
#### [NEW] `agents/rl/ppo_agent.py`
- PyTorch PPO implementation with actor-critic network
- State space: service list, alert count, foothold status, step number
- Action space: {scan-passive, scan-slow, scan-aggressive, exploit-http, exploit-ssh, exploit-ftp, patch-http, patch-ssh, patch-ftp, monitor}
- Trains via GPU (RTX 3060) in the training sandbox

#### [NEW] `agents/rl/experience_buffer.py`
- Replay buffer storing (state, action, reward, next_state, done)
- Agents learn from failed attempts: failed exploits get negative reward, successful patches get positive blue reward

#### [NEW] `agents/llm/reasoning_layer.py`
- Wraps Ollama (Llama3-8B) for high-level decision commentary
- Called after each episode to generate a "debrief" in natural language
- Also used for the final rating report

#### [NEW] `agents/memory/episode_store.py`
- SQLite-backed memory of past episodes
- Agents query: "what worked last time against this service config?"
- RAG-style retrieval of relevant past attempts

---

### 3. Training Sandboxes
#### [NEW] `sandbox/red_sandbox/docker-compose.yml`
- Isolated copy of environment — Red Team trains alone
- Faster episodes, no Blue interference
- `python train.py --agent red --episodes 500`

#### [NEW] `sandbox/blue_sandbox/docker-compose.yml`
- Blue Team trains against a scripted attacker to learn patching patterns

---

### 4. Professional Web UI (React + FastAPI)
#### [NEW] `ui/` (Vite + React)
- **Dashboard**: Live match feed, agent action log, real-time score chart
- **Training Lab**: Per-agent training controls (start/stop/resume), loss curves, reward graph
- **Rating Report**: Post-match CVSS-style PDF/HTML report
  - Attack surface coverage
  - Time-to-breach
  - Patch effectiveness
  - Overall security score (0–100)

#### [NEW] `api/dashboard_api.py`
- WebSocket endpoint for live match streaming to UI
- REST endpoints: `/train`, `/match/start`, `/report/generate`

---

### 5. Rating Report System
#### [NEW] `agents/report/generator.py`
- Generates structured HTML report after each match
- Sections: Executive Summary, Attack Timeline, Vulnerability Analysis, Recommendations
- CVSS-style scoring: Base Score = (AV + AC + PR + UI + S + CIA) / 6

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. `python -m pytest tests/test_rl_agent.py` — verify PPO policy updates after training loop
2. `python -m pytest tests/test_environment.py` — verify Docker services are reachable
3. `python train.py --agent red --episodes 10` — verify reward increases over episodes

### Manual Verification
1. Run `docker-compose up` — all 4 containers healthy
2. Open UI at `http://localhost:5173` — dashboard loads, match starts
3. After 1 episode: rating report generates with scores
